subSubSection.paragraph:
The range of distribution of the species is located in Western and Eastern Europe, from the British Isles (
Brooke and Nau 2003
) in the west to the Western Siberia and Central Asia in the east, from southern Finland in the north to Italy in the south (
Kanyukova 2006
). In the south of Russia, it is indicated from the North Caucasus (
Shapovalov et al. 2014
).The species was found in the Middle (our material) and South Urals (
Wroblewski 1963
). In the Ob Basin, the species was recorded from Novosibirsk (
Belevich and Yurchenko 2012
) and the south of Tyumen Regions (
Kanyukova et al. 2019
). It is known from the countries of Transcaucasia, Turkey, Kazakhstan (
Wroblewski 1963
), Kyrgyzstan, Tajikistan (
Jansson 1986
) and Northwest China (
Kanyukova et al. 2016
).
